# Myco forage/ default gitignore
# ================================
# ALL payload material is ignored by default. The manifest
# (_index.yaml) and README are the only things committed — that is
# the entire public trail. Payload stays LOCAL because:
#   (1) undigested raw material is not Myco's product; it would bloat
#       the public repo with content that hasn't been processed yet
#   (2) license coverage is highly uneven (proprietary articles,
#       unknown-license gists, author-owned text); safest default is
#       "don't republish"
#   (3) the digestion doctrine says payload is transient pre-note —
#       if it matters, it should survive as a note, not as raw bytes
#
# To commit a SPECIFIC item with an explicitly permissive license
# (CC-BY / MIT / Apache-2.0 / public domain / author consent), use:
#
#   git add -f forage/papers/<item>.pdf
#   git add -f forage/articles/<item>.md
#
# This is a conscious opt-in per item, not a default.
#
# Rationale: docs/primordia/forage_substrate_craft_2026-04-11.md §Round 1 A2 + R2.3
#            Wave 9 payload hygiene fix (2026-04-11)

# Binary papers
papers/**
!papers/.gitkeep

# Git clones
repos/**
!repos/.gitkeep

# All article payloads (html, md, pdf snapshots, etc.)
articles/**
!articles/.gitkeep

# Local cache / temp
.cache/
*.tmp
*.partial
